reviewText:
Intro
Back from Valhalla... MAX!
This game holds so many memories for me. The endless shootouts, the screaming of Max' wife, the babyroom-spaceout-wtf-mind♥♥♥♥, Bullet Time... too much to mention. This game is one of the first really bloody games i came in contact with, and at the age of twerlve, i never had any nightmares. Luskily, because this game is also set in a pretty sinister atmosphere.

Story in short
Working at the NYPD, Max is a hard working police detective. Three years ago his wife and kid got murdered by junkies, and he is remembered again when he rolls into a drug investigation. Soon he finds out that this drug and the murder of his family are connected. Desperate to cleanse the city from the drug and redeeming himself from the burden, he goes on a crusade. From an ease-in to a vertical dropdown in a rollercoaster, this game holds you by the balls from start to end.

Gameplay
this game is a ride, a flow. The game is divided by chapters, and obviously you start at Chapter 1. After loading screen mosly there is a quasi-funny comic, before you delve into the action. And action, well... no shortage of that. From one shootout to the next, blood everywhere, heroin syringes everywhere, painstillers everywhere... - I, for this very reason, do NOT recommend this game if you are sensitive for these things. I mean, if it's not the game, it is the amount of heroin ingame that makes you addicted to Max and his crusade. No, really...  MAN UP, YOU PRICK
Try to playthrough the game in it's hardest difficulty (Dead on Arrival) and you'll unlock a surprise. It's really worth it.

Pros  BULLET TIME;
the storyline. Yes, it's one of the game's top features;
the amount of blood;
BULLET TIME;
the rollercoaster ride from start to end;
the epic dark atmosphere;
BULLET TIME;
the graphics, still beatiful for todays standards;
the choice of weapons;
the EPIC quiting screen;
did i mention Bullet Time yet?
Cons  After a while you start to see a pattern
i hate those moments when you startle the ♥♥♥♥ out of NPC's coming suddenly into view...
... and killing you in an instant while you try to unload your whole mag on them. BULLETS, LOTS OF BULLETS
Apart from this, but not to be taken into consideration: The fact that i had difficulties installing and running the game in Windows 7 SP1. Why i don't take this into consideration? You can't expect a game built in the early 00's to be 100% compatible with multicored PC's imho, even when it's revamped. It's engine is just not built for multicore. You want the full experience, try it on a virtual machine, find an older PC or downgrade your PC. Please do not complain about this.

Conlusive
If you like dense packed action this is the game for you. I think this game is worth every penny, including when it's full price.

Gameplay        8.5                Visuals        9.5                Replay value        7.5            VERDICT        8.5/10
